Sandwich Monday: The Jim Shoe

   by Ian Chillag
   August 12, 2013 1:30 PM
   Behold. [26]Enlarge image [27]i

   Behold.
   NPR
   Behold.

   Behold.
   NPR

   The Chicago sandwich containing gyro meat, roast beef and corned beef
   goes by many names. This is one of many ways in which it's like the
   devil, and Sean Combs. People call it the Gym Shoe, the Jim Shoe or the
   Jim Shoo.

   Ian: With a name this unappetizing, the sandwich had no choice but to
   be so delicious no one would mess with it. It's like A Boy Named Shoe.

   Blythe: I thought I'd need my Reebok Stomach Pumps for this.
   Jim Shoe, or the world's most delicious Sarlacc? [28]Enlarge image
   [29]i

   Jim Shoe, or the world's most delicious Sarlacc?
   NPR
   Jim Shoe, or the world's most delicious Sarlacc?

   Jim Shoe, or the world's most delicious Sarlacc?
   NPR

   We went out to [30]Sony's Submarine to find one. They go with "Jim
   Shoe." You order through bulletproof glass and a sub shop worker passes
   you the goods through a little rotating door. This is not because it's
   a bad neighborhood or anything. A sandwich this important has to be
   wary of assassination attempts.

   Miles: I wish this had been the shoe of choice during my middle-school
   years. That way, everyone would've been ashamed to use the shower.

   Blythe: I feel like a fat Carrie Bradshaw right now.

   Ian: I never get this right â so it's pronounced "yee-roh" and
   "yastrointestinal distress," right?
   This is what it looks like when J.J. Abrams eats a Jim Shoe.
   [31]Enlarge image [32]i

   This is what it looks like when J.J. Abrams eats a Jim Shoe.
   NPR
   This is what it looks like when J.J. Abrams eats a Jim Shoe.

   This is what it looks like when J.J. Abrams eats a Jim Shoe.
   NPR

   Blythe: Kobe wears Kobes, Jordan wore Jordans and Jim, that guy who
   insists on "shirts" vs. "skins," wears Jims.

   Ian: I feel weird writing "Jim Shoe" instead of "Gym Shoe." Should I be
   adding [sic] or [sick]?
   Sony's did not have tables or chairs, so we ate out in the street.
   [33]Enlarge image [34]i

   Sony's did not have tables or chairs, so we ate out in the street.
   NPR
   Sony's did not have tables or chairs, so we ate out in the street.

   Sony's did not have tables or chairs, so we ate out in the street.
